They will wish to go out of the Fire, and they will not be brought forth therefrom, and theirs will be a lasting torment.
As for the thief, the male or female, and the women of the male, as a punishment from Allah; and Allah is Mighty, Wise.
But whoever repents after his crime and does good deeds, Allah will turn towards him; surely Allah is Forgiving, Merciful.
Do you not know that to Allah belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth? He punishes whom He pleases and forgives whom He pleases. And Allah has power over all things.
O Prophet! Do not grieve those who disbelieve, because they say to their mouths, "We believe in their mouths," and they say, "We believe," and their hearts do not have their faith. And those who are Jews and Christians do not come to you with a lie. They have not come to you with a lie. They say, "If you are commanded, you will be saved."
They listen to falsehood, but if they come to you, judge between them, or turn away from them. And if you turn away, they will not hurt you in the least. And if you judge them, judge between them with equity. God loves those who do good.
And how can they judge thee, when they have been given the Torah? In that case, they are in the presence of Allah, after they turn away, and they are not believers.
We have sent down the Torah, wherein is guidance and light; and the prophets and the rabbis and the rabbis and the Jews, who were commanded to observe the Book of God, and were witnesses against them. So do not fear the people, and have witnesses against them. Do not fear Me, and do not exchange My revelations for a small price.
And We decreed for them in the Book, the life of the eye, the nose, the nose, the nose, the nose, the tooth, for the tooth, and the tooth; and whoever remits the wounds, it shall be expiation for him; and whoever does not judge by what Allah has sent down, it shall be for him.
And We sent in their footsteps Jesus, son of Mary, confirming that which was before him of the Torah, and We gave him the Gospel, and the Gospel, and the light, and the Torah, and the Torah, and a guidance and a reminder for the righteous.
And the followers of the Book will judge according to what God has sent down, and those who do not judge according to what God has revealed.
And We have sent down to you the Book with the truth, confirming the Book which is before them, and that which has been sent down from the Book, and that which Allah has revealed to you. So follow what has been revealed to you, and do not follow their desires. And do not follow the desires of those who have come to the truth, and do not follow their desires. And if Allah had willed, He would have made you all.
And judge between them by what Allah has sent down, and follow not their desires, and beware of them lest they seduce you from some of what Allah has revealed to you. But if they turn away, know that Allah will punish them for their sins. And most of mankind are transgressors.
What do they desire to do, and who is better than the people who believe in God?
O you who believe! Do not take the Jews and the Christians for friends; they are friends of each other; and whoever among you takes them for a friend, then surely he is one of them; surely Allah does not guide the unjust people.
And you see those in whose hearts is a disease hastening towards them, saying, "We fear lest a misfortune befall us." So, God will bring them a victory, or a new command from Him, so that they may be remorseful.
And those who believe will say, "Are these the ones who swore by Allah that they are with you?" They will have their deeds, and they will be losers.
O you who have believed, whoever of you turns away from his religion, Allah will surely bring forth a people who will love Him and humble themselves to Him, who will strive against the believers, and they will strive hard in the way of Allah and do not fear the blame of a critic. Such is the bounty of Allah; and Allah is Ample-giving, Knowing.
Your guardian is only Allah and His Apostle and those who believe, and those who establish regular prayers and pay the poor-rate.
And whoever obeys Allah and His Messenger and those who believe, then surely the party of Allah will be the victors.
O you who have believed, do not take for those who have been given the Book and those who were before you as a joke and a joke for those who have been given the Book and the disbelievers, and fear Allah if you are believers.
And when you call to prayer, they take it as mockery and sport; this is because they are a people who do not understand.
Say: "O People of the Book! do you disapprove of us for no other reason than that we believe in Allah and what has been revealed to us and what was sent down before, and that most of you are transgressors?"
Say, "Shall I inform you of something worse than that which I possess? Those are the ones whom Allah has cursed, and the curse of those whom He has cursed, and some of whom He has made apes and swine. They are worse than the evil-doers.
When they come to you, they say, "We believe," but they have come to disbelief, and they go forth with it; and Allah knows best what they hide.
And you see many of them hastening away, and the devouring of the forbidden and the devouring, and evil is what they do.
Do they not forbid the rabbis and the rabbis and the women of their own selves? Evil is what they do.
And the Jews say: "Allah's plan is in the hand of Allah." They say: "Nay, they are cursed by what they say, and they are not proud of what they say; nay, it is in the hands of Allah that He may make it known to you. And that which He pleases, and that which He pleases, and that which is in the earth. And We make enmity between them and those who do mischief in the land. And Allah loveth not those who make mischief.
And if the People of the Book had believed and feared Allah, We would certainly have removed from them their sins and admitted them to gardens of bliss.
And if they had observed the Torah and the Gospel and what has been sent down to them from their Lord, they would have been provided from above them and from beneath their feet. Some of them are a people who have gone astray.
O Messenger! deliver what has been revealed to you from your Lord; and if you do it not, then you have not delivered His message, and Allah will protect you from the people; and Allah will not guide the unbelieving people.
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "O People of the Book (Jews and Christians), ye shall not stand on the ground until ye stand up until the Taurat (Torah) and the Injeel (Gospel), and that which has been sent down to you from your Lord, and that which has been sent down to you from your Lord will increase many of them in inordinacy and disbelief. So do not grieve for the disbelievers.
Those who believe, and those who are Jews, and the Sabians, and the Christians, and the Christians, whoever believes in Allah and the Last Day and does good, they shall have no fear nor shall they grieve.
We made a covenant with the Children of Israel and We sent messengers to them. When there came to them a messenger with what they did not desire, some of them they denied, and some they killed.
And they thought that there is no trial, so they became deaf and deaf; then Allah has shown them mercy, so that many of them are deaf and deaf. And Allah sees what they do.
Those who disbelieve say, "The Messiah, son of Mary, is God's son." And the Messiah said, "O Children of Israel, worship Allah, my Lord and your Lord." But whoever associates with Allah, He will admit him into the garden, and his abode will be the fire; and the unjust will be a helper.
Those who say, "Allah is the third of three." There is no god but He. And if they do not desist from what they say, the disbelievers will not desist from the painful torment.
Will they not then turn to Allah and seek His forgiveness? And Allah is Forgiving, Merciful.
The Messiah, son of Mary, was no more than a messenger. There were many messengers before him, and his mother was one of the truth. And his mother ate food. See how We make clear to them the signs; so see how they are turned away.
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "Do you worship besides Allah that which can neither profit you nor benefit you? Allah is Hearing, Knowing."
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "O people of the Book (Jews and Christians), do not exaggerate in your religion in the religion of truth, nor follow the desires of the people who went astray before, and many misled many and misled many of the way."
Those who disbelieved among the Children of Israel were cursed by the tongue of David and Jesus, the son of Mary. That was because they disobeyed and persisted in excesses.
They did not forbid one another from what they used to do. Evil is what they used to do.
You see many of them befriending those who disbelieve. Evil is that which their souls have sent before them, and that God's wrath is that which they have been, and they will abide in the punishment of eternal punishment.
And if they believed in Allah and the Prophet and what was revealed to him, they would not have taken them for friends, but most of them are transgressors.
You will surely find the most hostile of the Jews and the idolaters in the sight of the believers, and you will see those who say, "We are Christians," and those who say, "We are Christians".
And when they hear what has been revealed to the Messenger, you see their eyes overflowing with tears because they recognize the truth; they say: Our Lord! we believe, so write us down among the witnesses.
And what aileth us that we should not believe in Allah and the truth which has come to us, and that our Lord will admit us to the company of the righteous?
So Allah has prepared for them that which they say, with gardens beneath which rivers flow, abiding therein forever; and this is the reward of the righteous.
And those who disbelieve and deny Our Signs, they are the companions of the Fire.
O you who believe! Do not forbid the good things which Allah has made lawful for you, and do not transgress limits; surely Allah loves not transgressors.
And eat of that which Allah has provided for you, lawful and good, and fear Allah in Whom you are believers.
Allah will not force you to account for the oaths that you will not seize your oaths, and if you do not swear, then you will not be able to kill the souls of your souls, and that you may eat the souls of the souls of the souls of the people, or if you are poor.
O you who believe! intoxicants and gambling, and idols and divining arrows are an abomination of Satan. So avoid that which you may prosper.
Satan wants to excite enmity and hatred between you and intoxicants and gambling, and hinder you from the remembrance of Allah and prayer. Will you not then abstain?
And obey Allah and obey the Messenger and fear Him. If you turn away, know that Our duty is only to convey the duty of Our Messenger.
Those who believe and do deeds of righteousness, there is no sin on what they eat, and they believe, and believe, and do righteous deeds, and they fear God and believe in Him, and believe in Him; and Allah loves those who do good.
O you who believe! Allah will test you through what you have earned or your lances, and that Allah may test those who fear Him, and whoever turns away after that, there is a painful punishment for him.
O you who believe! Do not be thankful for the sake of the people of the world. And whoever among you dies, then surely he dies, and he who dies, then He gives you a double of what he has given you. It is not lawful for you to die, or the poor, or the poor, or those who do not believe in the cause of Allah. That is the recompense of those who do evil deeds. And Allah is Mighty, Mighty.
It is lawful for you to eat of the sea, and to eat for you, and to provide for you a provision and a provision; and the land is forbidden for you. And fear Allah and be wary of Him.
God has made the Ka'bah, the Sacred House, the Sacred House, the Sacred Month, and the Month and the Month, that you may know that you know that Allah knows what is in the heavens and the earth; and Allah knows all things.
Know that Allah is severe in punishment and that Allah is Forgiving and Merciful.
The duty of the Messenger is only to convey the message, and Allah knows what you reveal and what you conceal.
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "The good and the bad are not equal, even though the abundance of the bad may attract you. So fear Allah, so that you may be successful."
O you who have believed, do not ask about things which has been made clear to you, if it is clear to you, and if you ask about them, they will be made manifest to you. God has pardoned you. God is Forgiving and Forbearing.
A people before you asked about it, and they disbelieved in it.
God has not made any Bahirah, nor Wasilah, nor Wasilah, nor Hami, but they deny the lie of God, and most of them do not understand.
And when it is said to them, "Come to what Allah has sent down and to the Messenger," they say, "Sufficient for us is that which we found our fathers doing." Even even though their fathers knew not, nor were they guided.
O you who believe! Be careful to your souls. If you are guided, no harm can hurt you. To Allah you will be returned to all that you did. He will inform you of what you used to do.
O you who believe! If death approaches one of you, then two two months are two; but if they are in the land, they will be among you, or other than you. And when you are dead, then surely you will be able to stand in the land, and if you have a doubt, then if you have no doubt, then let them swear by the name of Allah, and they will swear allegiance to Allah. And We will surely tell you the interpretation of the truth.
But if they know that they are guilty of sin, then two men have two nearest to one another, and they swear by Allah, that they may bear witness to the testimony of their testimony, and that they should not have been slain, and we have not transgressed.
It may be that it may be better for them, or fear their oaths after their oaths. And fear Allah, and listen to him. And Allah does not guide the disobedient people.
On the Day when Allah will gather all the messengers together, and will say: What is what you have been given? They will say: We have no knowledge. You are the Knower of all things.
And when Jesus, the son of Mary, said, "My Lord, remember Me, and my mother, and all that I have bestowed upon you, and the Holy Spirit, which I have bestowed upon you, and the people who are in the Book, and that which is in the Book of God, and that which is in the midst of the Book and the Gospel."
And when I inspired the disciples to believe in Me and My Messenger, they said, "We believe and bear witness that we are Muslims."
When the disciples said, "O Jesus, son of Mary, will your Lord send down to us a table from heaven?" He said, "Fear God, if you are believers."
They said, "We wish that we may eat from it, and that our hearts may know that you are truthful."
“Jesus, son of Mary, said, ‘O Allah, our Lord, send down to us a table from heaven, to be a festival for us and the last of us and the last of us and a sign from You.
He said, "I will send it down to you, but whoever of you disbelieves in me, I will punish him with a severe punishment."
And when Allah will say, "O Jesus, son of Mary, did you say to the people, 'Take my mother and my mother?' He will say, "You are the glory of God." He will say, "You say, 'You are not truthful.'
"Never said I to them aught except what Thou didst command me to say: worship Allah, my Lord and your Lord."
If You punish them, they are Your servants; and if You forgive them, indeed You are the Mighty, the Wise.
Allah will say: "This is a day on which the truthful will profit their truthfulness, for them are Gardens beneath which rivers flow, abiding therein forever. Allah is well pleased with them and they are well pleased with Him. That is the great success."
To Allah belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth and all that is in them, and He has power over all things.
All praise belongs to Allah, Who created the heavens and the earth and made the light light and light; then those who disbelieve ascribe equals to their Lord.
He it is Who created you from clay, then decreed a term, and a term (of a term); then there is a term in which you doubt.
And He is Allah in the heavens and on earth; He knows what you conceal and what you reveal; and He knows what you earn.
There is no sign from their Lord, but they turn away from it.
They denied the truth when it came to them, but they will come to them.
Have they not seen how many a generation We have destroyed before them, and We established on the earth, that We had not established you, and We caused them to grow on the sky, beneath which rivers flow, and We caused them to grow in the rivers, and We have made them a generation of their sins, and after them We have created the nations of the earth?
And if We had sent down to you a Book on paper, and they had touched it with their hands, those who disbelieved would say: This is nothing but obvious magic.
And they say, "Why has not an angel been sent down to him?" Had We sent down the angels, it would have been decreed for them, but they would not be respited.
And if We had made him an angel, We would certainly have made him a man, and We would have made them doubt concerning what they have been confused.
Messengers have been derided before thee, but those who scoffed surrounded them, that they scoffed at them.
Say: Travel in the land and see how was the end of the deniers.
Say: "To whom belongs all that is in the heavens and on earth?" Say: "To Allah belongs all that is in the heavens and on the Day of Resurrection. He will gather you together on the Day of Resurrection concerning the Day of Resurrection.
And to Him belongs whatever is in the night and the day; and He is the Hearing, the Knowing.
Say, "Shall I take for myself a guardian other than Allah, the Maker of the heavens and the earth? He feeds and gives no provision. Say: "I am commanded to be the first of those who submit to Him, and He will not be of the idolaters."
Say, "If I disobey my Lord, I fear the punishment of a tremendous Day."
On that Day, whoever is averted from it, Allah has indeed shown mercy to him, and that is the manifest triumph.
And if Allah touches you with affliction, none can remove it but He; and if He touches you with good, He has power over all things.
And He is the All-Mighty, the All-Wise.
Ask them, "What is the greater testimony?" Say, "I testify that God is witness to me and you, and I testify that the Qur'an has been revealed to you." It is revealed that it is revealed to you, and to those who warn the truth, and to warn those who are near to the truth. Do you think that there is no god but Allah? Say, "I am only a god."
Those to whom We have given the Book recognize it as they recognize their own sons. Those who do not believe will not believe.
Who is more unjust than one who invents a lie against Allah or rejects His Signs? Indeed, the wrongdoers do not prosper.
And on the Day when We shall gather them all together, then We will say to those who associated partners with Allah, "Where are your partners whom you used to assert?"
Then there shall be no excuse for them except that they say: By our Lord, we were not idolaters.
See how they lied against themselves, and that which they used to invent.
And among them are those who listen to thee, and We have put veils on their hearts, lest they understand it, and deafness in their ears; but if they see every sign, they will not believe in it. When they come to thee, they say: This is nothing but tales of the ancients.
And they forbid it, and they turn away from it, and they do not destroy themselves, but they do not know.
And if you could see when they are made to stand before the Fire, they will say, "Oh, would that we had been returned, and we would not deny the signs of our Lord, and we would be among the believers."
Nay, but that which they hide before them are manifest to them; but if they return to it, they shall revert to what they have been forbidden, and verily they are liars.
And they say: "There is nothing but our life of this world, and we shall not be raised again."
And if you see them, when they are made to stand before their Lord, He will say, "Is this not real?" They will say, "Yes, by our Lord," and He will say, "Then taste the punishment for what you used to disbelieve."
Those who deny the meeting with Allah will be lost. Until when the Hour comes on them suddenly, they say, "Alas for us!" And they will bear their burdens on their backs, and they will bear their burdens on their backs.
The life of this world is nothing but a sport and a sport; and the home of the Hereafter is better for those who fear Allah. Will you not then understand?
We know that what they say grieves you. It is not you who deny it, but the wrongdoers deny the signs of Allah.
Messengers were denied before thee, but they endured patiently, and they endured patiently, until Our help came to them. And there is none to change the words of Allah. And there has come to you the Messengers of the messengers.
And if their aversion is hard for you, then if you seek a tunnel into the earth or a ladder to the sky, then bring them a sign, and if Allah had so willed, He would have brought them all guidance, so do not be of the ignorant.
Those who hear (the truth) listen to the call of Allah, and those who are dead will be resurrected, and they will be returned to Him.
They say, "Why has not a sign been sent down to him from his Lord?" Say, "God is able to send down a sign, but most of them do not know."
And there is not a creature on earth nor a bird flying on its wings, but they are like you as communities; We have not neglected anything in the Book; then to their Lord they will be gathered.
And those who deny Our signs are deaf and dumb in darkness; whom Allah wills, He leaveth astray; and whomsoever He pleases, He placeth on the right way.
Say, "Have you considered, if the punishment of Allah comes upon you or the Hour comes upon you, will you call upon other than Allah if you are truthful?"
Nay, but you call upon Him, and if He wills, He will remove it from you, and you will forget what you associate with Him.
We sent Messengers before you, and afflicted them with distress and hardship that they might humble themselves.
So why did they not worship Him when Our punishment came to them, and their hearts were hardened, and Satan has made them seem attractive to what they did.
So when they forgot that which they had been reminded, We opened them to the gates of all things, and when they had been blessed, We seized them suddenly, and they became in despair.
And the people of the evildoers were cut off, and all praise be to Allah, the Lord of the worlds.
Say, "Have you considered, if God should take away your hearing and your sight and set up a seal upon your hearts, who can bring it to you to bring you back to God?
Say: "Tell me, if the punishment of Allah comes upon you suddenly or openly, will any one be destroyed except the unjust?"
And We send not the Messengers but as bearers of good tidings and warners; but those who believe and mend their ways shall have no fear, nor shall they grieve.
And for those who deny Our signs, they will suffer the punishment of a painful punishment.
Say, "I do not say to you that I possess the treasuries of God, nor do I know the unseen, nor do I say to you that I am an angel. I follow only what is revealed to me. Say, "Are the blind and the blind?" Do you not reflect?
And warn those who fear their Lord, that they will be gathered to their Lord, and they will have no protector nor intercessor, that they may guard against evil.
And do not turn away those who call upon their Lord in the morning and at the evening, seeking His countenance. They do not have any account for you, nor are you accountable for them, nor are you responsible for them.
So We test some of them with some of them, so that they say, "Are these those whom Allah has favoured us?"
And when those who believe in Our Signs come to you, say: Peace be upon you; your Lord has inscribed mercy upon Himself; so that if any of you does evil in ignorance, and thereafter repents and amend, then He is Forgiving, Merciful.
And thus do We explain the signs, so that the path of the wicked may be manifest.
Say, "I am forbidden to worship those whom you invoke besides Allah. Say, "I do not follow your desires; I have gone astray, and I am not of the guided ones."
Say, "I have been clear to you from my Lord, and you deny it. I am not responsible for what you hasten. This is nothing but Allah's command, and He is the best of judges."
Say: "If I had been asked for that which you were asking, I would have been settled between you and you. God knows best the wrongdoers."
And with Him are the keys of the unseen. He knows what is in the land and the sea; and He knows what is in the land and the sea; and there is not a grain but a leaf, nor a grain of the earth, nor is it in the earth, nor can it be a manifest Book.
And He it is Who takes your souls by night, and He knows what you have done by day, then He raises you up, that a term appointed be fulfilled; then to Him is your return, then He will inform you of what you did.
And He is the Omnipotent over His servants, and He sends guardians over you; when death approaches one of you, Our angels will die, and they do not perceive.
Then they will be returned to Allah, the True, the True. That is the command of Allah; and He is the swiftest in reckoning.
Say, "Who delivers you from the darkness of the land and the sea, when you call upon Him humbly and secretly? If He delivers us from this, we will surely be among the thankful."
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "It is Allah Who delivers you from them and from every distress, then you ascribe partners to Him."
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "He has power to punish you from above you from above you or from beneath your feet, or to bring you into sects into sects, and to make you taste some of the violence of others. See how We explain the communications to you that they may understand."
And your people deny it, and it is the truth. Say: I am not a guardian over you.
For every time there is an appointed time, and you will know.
And when you see those who dispute concerning Our signs, turn away from them until they engage in other discourse; and if Satan makes you forget, then do not sit after the people of the evildoers.
And those who guard (against evil) will not be able to hasten on them on account of their deeds, but they are admonished, so that they may fear.
And (as for) those who take their religion, and sport and sport, and give them the life of this world, and do not remind them of the Qur'an, and do not forget the Qur'an, nor will he be able to take it out of their own soul. And if they do not have any protector, it will not be accepted from them. They will have no protector and a painful punishment.
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "Shall we worship besides Allah that which does not profit us, nor will He hurt us, and that which Allah has guided us, and that which they returned to their backs?
And (that is) the prayer (of prayer) and fear Him, and He is the One to Whom you will be gathered.
It is He who has created the heavens and the earth in truth; and on the day when He will say, "Be!" and it is; and His Word is the truth; and on the Day when the Trumpet shall be blown, and the Trumpet shall be blown; and He is the Wise, the Wise.
And when Abraham said to his father Azar, "Do you take idols for idols? I will see you and your people in manifest error."
Thus did We show Abraham the kingdom of the heavens and the earth, that he might be of those who have faith.
When the night covered him, he saw a star, and he said, "This is my Lord;" but when it set, he said, "I do not love what I do."
When he saw the moon rising, he said, "This is my Lord;" but when it set, he said, "If my Lord does not guide me, I will surely be among the people who go astray."
When he saw the sun rising, he said, "This is my Lord; this is greater than this." When it set, he said, "O my people, I am quit of what you associate with Him."
“I have turned to Him who has created the heavens and the earth, and I am not of the idolaters.”
And his people disputed with him. He said, "Do you dispute with me concerning Allah, that He has guided me, and I do not fear that which you associate with Him? My Lord comprehends all things in knowledge. Will you not remember?"
And how should I fear that which you associate with Him, while you do not fear that you have associated with Allah what He has not sent down to you, but if you know that the two parties is better than the two parties?
Those who believe and do not follow their faith, for them is a secure security, and they are rightly guided.
And this was Our argument which We gave to Abraham against his people. We raise in degrees whomsoever We please; surely your Lord is Wise, Knowing.
And We gave Ibrahim (Abraham) Isaac and Ya'qub, and We guided him, and We guided Noah and his family, and of his progeny, and of the progeny of David and Solomon and Job and Aaron and Aaron and Aaron, and thus do We reward those who do good.
And Zakariya and John and Jesus and Elias, and all of them are righteous.
And Ishmael, and Elisha, and Jonah, and Lot, and all the people of the worlds.
And among their fathers and their descendants and their brothers, and We chose them, and We guided them on the Straight Path.
Such is the guidance of Allah; He guides whom He pleases.
These are those whom We gave to the Book, and the wisdom, and the prophethood; but if they disbelieve in it, We have made a people a people who deny not.
Those are the ones whom Allah has guided, so follow your guidance. Say, "I do not ask any reward for you. This is a reminder for the worlds."
And they did not have a covenant with Allah, because they said, "What has been sent down to us from Allah?" Say, "He has sent down the Book and the Gospel." Say, "We have been sent down to the Book of Moses and the guidance of the people." Say, "We have been sent down to you, and you do not know what you were doing." Say, "God has given you the Book." Say, "This is the Book."
And this is the Book which We have sent down, confirming that which is before it, and that you may warn the Mother of Cities and those around it, and those who believe in the Hereafter believe in it, and they are obedient to their prayers.
And who is more unjust than one who invents a lie against Allah or says, "It has been revealed to me," and he has been sent down to him, or he says, "I am sent down to the Book," or if you do not see what God has sent down, and if you see the angels, the angels will have a humiliating punishment.
And indeed you have come to Us as We created you first, and you left behind your backs, and We have not seen you with your intercessors, and We see not with you those whom you asserted that you asserted that you were partners.
It is Allah Who brings forth the grain and the date-tree, the living and the dead, and He brings forth the living from the dead and the dead. That is Allah, how you are turned away.
He is the One Who makes the dawn, and He has made the night for rest, and the sun and the moon, and the sun and the moon; this is the decree of the Almighty, the Knowing.
And it is He Who has made the stars for you, that you may be able to guide them in the darkness of the land and the sea; indeed We have made clear to you the signs for a people who know.
And He it is Who has created you from a single soul, and then a resting place and a resting-place; indeed We have made clear to you the signs for a people who understand.
And He it is Who sends down water from the sky, then We bring forth therewith of it all kinds of plants, and of which We have brought forth fruits, from which We bring forth crops of date trees, trees and pomegranates, and the fruits of date-trees, and the fruits and the pomegranates, and the fruits, and the fruits, and the fruits, and it is the fruits of the living.
And they ascribe to the jinn with the jinn, and He has created them, and they falsely ascribe themselves to Him, and ascribe sons and daughters. Glory be to Him! High is He above what they ascribe to Him.
Who is the Creator of the heavens and the earth? How can He have a son, and He has no consort, and He created all things, and He has knowledge of all things?
Such is Allah, your Lord; there is no god but He, the Creator of all things; therefore worship Him, and He is the Guardian of all things.
Vision comprehends Him not; He comprehends all things, and He is the Subtle, the Aware.
Indeed, there has come to you clear proofs from your Lord; so whoever sees, it is for his own good; and whoever blinds himself, it is to his own loss; and I am not a keeper over you.
And thus do We explain the signs, and that they may say, "You have studied," and that We may make it clear to a people who know.
Follow what has been revealed to you from your Lord, there is no god but He, and turn away from the polytheists.
And if Allah had willed, they would not have associated others with Him, and We have not made you a keeper over them, and you are not a keeper over them.
Do not insult those whom they invoke besides Allah, lest they should revile Allah in ignorance. Thus We have made their deeds fair-seeming to them, and to their Lord is their return, and He will inform them of what they did.
And they swear by Allah with their strongest oaths that if a sign came to them, they would believe in it. Say: "These signs are with Allah." Say: "If only they believe, they will not believe."
And We shall turn their hearts and their eyes, and they will not believe in it, and We will leave them in their rebellion in their rebellion.
