And thus have We made for every Prophet an enemy from among the jinn and the jinn, and some of the jinn, who inspire each other with speech, and made it an object of discourse, so that if your Lord had so willed, they would not have done it. So leave them alone.
And that the hearts of those who do not believe in the Hereafter may incline to it, and that they may be pleased with it, and that they may be the ones who do what they are doing.
Shall I seek other than Allah as a judge? He has sent down to you the Book. Those who have been given the Book know that it is the truth from your Lord. So do not be among the doubters.
And the word of thy Lord doth find its fulfilment and justice. None can change His words; and He is the Hearing, the Knowing.
And if you obey most of those on earth, they will lead you astray from the path of Allah.
Your Lord knows best who has gone astray from His path, and He knows best those who are guided.
If you believe in God, then you have to believe in Him.
