And when a sign comes to them, they say, "We will not believe until we have been given the Messengers of God." Allah knows best what He sent to His servants, and those who commit evil will have a painful punishment.
And whomsoever Allah wills to guide, He opens his heart to Islam; and whomsoever He wills to go astray, He makes his heart narrow and constricted, as if he were climbing into the sky. Those who do not believe in the way of Allah will be punished.
This is the Straight Path of your Lord. We have explained Our signs for a people who remember.
For them is a place of security for their Lord, and He is their guardian.
And on the Day when He will gather them all together, and say, "O assembly of jinn, many of you have been weak." The people of the people say, "Our Lord, we have made some of us one of another." Then, when We have given you a term, then say, "Your abode is hell." He will say, "Your abode is hell." And God is Wise, Knowing.
And thus We have made the wrongdoers friends of one another, because of what they used to do.
O assembly of jinn and men, did not Messengers come to you from among yourselves, reciting to you My signs and warning you of this Day of yours? They will say, "We bear witness against ourselves." They will say, "We bear witness against them." They will bear witness against themselves. They will bear witness against themselves.
That is because your Lord did not destroy the cities unjustly while their people were unaware.
And all of them are in ranks, and your Lord is not unaware of what they do.
Your Lord is Self-sufficient, All-merciful. If He wills, He will destroy you and bring you to the successors, and He will raise you up as He pleases you.
Verily, the promise which you have been promised will surely come to pass.
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "O my people! Work according to your deeds, and I am rightly-doing. Soon you will come to know that the reward of the Hereafter will be the end of the Hereafter; surely the unjust will not prosper.
