Are they waiting for the angels, or the angels, or some of the signs of your Lord? On the Day when the signs of your Lord will come to pass, the people will not believe in it, nor will they believe. Say, "Wait, we are waiting." Say, "Wait, we too are waiting."
As for those who divide their religion and became sects, you have no share in them. Their affair is with Allah; then He will inform them of what they did.
Whoever brings a good deed shall receive a harvest like it; and whoever does evil, it shall be recompensed for him, and they will not be wronged.
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "Verily, my Lord has guided me to a straight path, a religion of religion, the religion of Abraham, the upright, and he was not of the polytheists."
Say: "Verily, my prayer, my sacrifice, my living and my dying are for Allah, the Lord of the Worlds."
There is no partner in Him, and I am commanded to be the first of those who submit to Him.
Say: "Shall I seek other than Allah as Lord, and He is the Lord of all things?"
