"O Adam! dwell thou and thy wife in the Garden, and eat of it wherever ye desire; but approach not this tree, lest ye be of the wrongdoers."
Then Satan whispered to them that he might manifest to them what was hidden from them of their shame, and he said, "Your Lord, save you from this tree lest you should become angels or become immortal."
And he swore to them, saying, "I am a sincere adviser to you."
So he caused them to fall down; so when they tasted their nakedness, their shame became manifest to them; and their Lord called them out of the Garden, and did not say to you, "Did I not forbid you that Satan is an open enemy to you?"
They said, "Our Lord, we have wronged ourselves, and if You do not forgive us and have mercy on us, we will surely be among the losers."
(Allah) said: "Go ye down, for ye are enemies of one another, and for the earth there is a place of enjoyment and provision for a time."
He said, "Therein you shall live, and therein you shall die, and from it you shall be brought forth."
O children of Adam! We have sent down to you a garment that may cover your nakedness, and a garment, and a garment, and the garment of piety; this is the best of the signs, so that they may remember.
O Children of Adam! Let not Satan seduce you, as he got your parents out of the Garden, stripping them of their raiment, to expose them their shame; and he and his tribe watch you from a position where ye cannot see them. We made the devils friends for those who believe.
And when they commit an indecency, they say, "We found our fathers doing it," and God commanded us. Say: "Why do Allah not command such an indecency?" Say, "Allah does not command indecency."
Say: "My Lord has commanded justice, and set your faces at every place of worship, and call upon Him, making the religion sincerely to Him. He created you as He created you, so you will return."
He has guided the people, and some of them are misguided. They have taken the devils for friends instead of Allah, and they think that they are rightly guided.
O children of Adam! wear your apparel at every time of worship, and eat and drink and drink, but do not be excessive, for God loves not the wasters.
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "Who has forbidden the adornment of Allah which He has brought forth for His servants and the good things?" Say: "This is for those who believe in this world and on the Day of Resurrection. Thus do We explain the signs for those who know."
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "My Lord has forbidden me (all) that is shameful and open, and that which is hidden, and that which is hidden, and that you associate with Allah that for which He has no authority, and that you say concerning Allah that which you do not know."
And every nation shall have a term; when their term comes, they shall not be able to delay a single hour, nor shall they precede it.
