He will say: "Enter the fire of Hell, which you have gone before, and those who were before you, and the people of the nations, when it will be as a destruction, and when it will come to pass, the last of them will say, 'Our Lord! Our Lord! You have led us astray, so that He may punish them for a double punishment.' He will say: "This is a double punishment."
And the first of them will say, "You have not been arrogant for us, so taste the punishment for what you used to earn."
As for those who reject Our signs and treat them with arrogance, the gates of heaven will not be opened, nor will they enter Paradise until the camel passes through the eye of the needle. Thus do We recompense the guilty.
For them shall be a bed of fire and folds over them; and thus do We recompense the unjust.
And as for those who believe and do good deeds, We impose no burden on any soul beyond its capacity; these are the dwellers of the Garden; therein shall they abide.
And We shall remove from them what is in their hearts, and rivers flow beneath them, and they will say, "Praise be to Allah, Who has guided us." If Allah had not guided us, we would not have been guided, and we would not have been guided. Our Lord has brought the truth to you.
And the dwellers of Paradise will call out to the dwellers of the Fire: "We have indeed found that which our Lord promised us to be true. Have you found what your Lord promised you to be true?" They will say, "Yes," and a crier will call between them.
Those who hinder (men) from the way of Allah and seek to make it crooked, and they do not believe in the Hereafter.
And there shall be a barrier between them and on the heights, and on the heights will be men who recognize their marks, and they will call out to the dwellers of Paradise, "Peace be upon you." They will not enter it, but they will have hope.
